<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,292,152,179]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">Colour:</emphasis>
Head and pronotum reddish brown; head with labrum and edges of clypeus reddish yellow coloured, rest reddish brown; pronotum with lateral margin black; antennal segments 1–4 light reddish yellow, segments 5–11 dark brown; elytra black; legs reddish yellow with large black spot on the apex of the femur.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,152,719]" box="[199,983,260,287]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,272,261,287]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">Head:</emphasis>
Narrower than pronotum; disc smooth; eyes highly protruding.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,329,297,323]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">Pronotum:</emphasis>
Wider than the head, as long as wide, square shaped; anterior margin truncated squarely; disc smooth without wrinkles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,285,369,395]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">Elytra:</emphasis>
Subparallel, narrowed towards the base, elytral base and apex squared; humerus straight, prominent; the median transverse band ‘dagger shaped’, transverse, margins strongly serrated, dilated near the outer edge that it does not reach, and truncated squarely by the 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[678,694,439,453]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">nd</superScript>
striation; apical yellow band broader covering the intervals.
</paragraph>
