<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,657,683]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">Remarks.</emphasis>
Very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1886" box="[503,619,657,682]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pheropsophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catoirei">
<emphasis box="[503,619,657,682]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">P. catoirei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differs by the shape of pronotum which is as wide as long and square shaped, not narrowing posteriorly; elytral median transverse band is more transverse, more serrated at its edges.
</paragraph>
